info.name: Gmail: Native Google Attachment Icons
info.description:
See what type of file is attached to a conversation or message before opening it.

Inspired by similar styles, this replaces Gmail’s paper clip for attachments, both in list view and in conversation view, with icons from Google Drive. Conversations with multiple attachments show a folder icon.
info.additionalInfo: If you see a paper clip, then you have an attachment that is not detected. If you tell me the file’s extension, I can try to include it. Changelog 2016-08-04: Fixed bug, thanks to user 257296. Also added ePUB. 2014-04-02: Added separate icon for plain text files.

data.title: Great work.  Should be a native feature.
How to Move Icon Column Next to the Star?
